<br>
Have things changed at all?<br>
<br>
1) Did they fix defensive skills like evadeclsc, or evade-range<br>
2) Do we still do minimum damage after about level 60<br>
3) We ever get a helm to match our armor <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
4) How are the special attacks now?<br>
5) I think i read that the &quot;fist&quot; line finally does change our damage type, is that true?<br>
6) Is phys-init still worthless (i.e. the change is so small ya dont notice it)<br>
<br>
Whats the overall opinion of the MA? Are we still basically a back up doctor, who can buff a crit bonus, and then do subpar damage? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/uiccusion.showPublicProfile?language=EN>iccusion</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Peking Duck</span><br>  Posts: 166<br> <font color=#660000>(10/22/02 3:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2144.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Another Returning MA</span><hr size=1> Welcome back!  I think the OFFICIAL &quot;Patch From Hell&quot; was 12.6, btw.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
<br>
Here are the answers to your questions, and it is almost entirely good news (from an MA perspective):<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> &quot;Did they fix defensive skills like evadeclsc, or evade-range?&quot;<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Mostly.  Evades <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> do</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> work, and they work even more effectively when you modify your settings with the agg/def bar.  Now you even get visible confirmation of evades with messages like <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> &quot;Veteran Thug tried to hit you, but missed!&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> each time you evade an attack, and vice versa.  Parry now works the same way.  The bad news is that many Mobs have ridiculous Evades and Parry skills that are WAAAAY out of line with their effective &quot;level&quot;.  (In other words, Mobs are incredibly uber compared to players of the same level.  This is supposedly to help make up for AO's utterly lacking AI.)<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> &quot;Do we still do minimum damage after about level 60&quot;<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Nope.  Thankfully, those days are long gone.  MAs got some serious lovin' from FunCom in patch 13.8/13.9 (IIRC), and when running our crit buffs we are now pretty much the profession with best damage over time...as the game designers have always claimed was &quot;the way it <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> should</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> be&quot;.  MAs can solo better than nearly any other profession (IMHO), and we are coveted in teams for our superior damage.  If you do come back, be prepared to tank when teaming (in other words, keep your evades and ACs up to date...).<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> &quot;We ever get a helm to match our armor?&quot;<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->If you are talking about the decus armor which is very popular among MAs due to the Agil/Str requirements, then, Yes, there is a helm.  If you are talking about the Martial Artist Suit armor type, then, No, there is still no helm.  The MA Suit armor is, surprisingly, not really the best armor for MAs anyway (IMHO), with Flowers Tech and Decus armor being the most popular for Agil/Str types, and Obtru being the most popular for Opifex MAs using Agil/Sense armor types. But your own mileage may vary. (Many crusty old players may remember when Decus armor was SOCIAL armor only.  It is now &quot;regular armor&quot; and very common as a mission reward.)  Recent additions also include some really nice MA &quot;Organic Combat Suits&quot; for back armor (superior in many ways to the ever-popular Decus Armor Coats), and they come in a variety of colors, with each color adding a bit to different stats.  Finally, Servants of Eight MA armor pieces were also added recently, and they were supposed to be really nice MA equipment with skill bonuses for each piece, but they have some really dumb-ass level requirements which are WAY out of whack, rendering them pretty much useless (since by the time you meet the level req, you can wear MUCH MUCH better &quot;standard&quot; armor).  MA Organic Combat Suits and So8 armor are Boss Loot only.  (Bosses are found at the end of Team missions as well as in special outdoor camps.)<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> &quot;How are the special attacks now?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Not all that different.  Due to the length of skill locks on most of them and their effectiveness, BwT is still pretty much the special of choice for PvM.  Shen still kicks ass in PvP, and Attack of the Snake and Bird of Prey are useful until you can start using BwT at around 30th level.  Flower of Life is STILL broken except for exactly Q60 and Q200, and nearly all good MA special attacks are now mission loot only (Yup, they took the good ones out of the shops).  I saw some slight changes in the test database for 14.6, but it mostly looked like they FINALLY got around to making each special's icon slightly different.  Didn't really see any major changes to the attacks themselves or the length of the skill locks.<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> &quot;I think i read that the &quot;fist&quot; line finally does change our damage type, is that true?&quot;<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Yes, but it's really not THAT big a deal.  It helps some in PvP if your opponent is especially vulnerable to a particular damage type, but in PvM it is mostly a wash.  Also, it makes any MA become a real &quot;Lord of the Rings&quot;, since you need to have and use the correct Power rings in order to add anything to your fist damage.  Wearing a <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> +12 Ring of Power: Melee</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> ring doesn't do anything for you if you are running Fists of the Lightning Crane, for example.<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> &quot;Is phys-init still worthless (i.e. the change is so small ya dont notice it)?&quot;<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Phys Init has never really been &quot;useless&quot;, just very misunderstood by most.  Inits are part of a very complex AO combat mechanism, and as such, are still not completely understood by even the serious game-mechanics-oriented players (myself included).  In short, however, MA fists are a 1.25s attack/1.25s recharge &quot;weapon&quot;, and since AO does not ever allow a weapon to strike faster than 1s/1s for attack/recharge, at about 150 Phys Init or so MAs &quot;top out&quot; at full speed when at 100% aggressive on their agg/def slider.  But although having, say...650 Phys Init will never let you hit faster than 1s/1s at full aggro, it DOES allow you to still hit at full speed at about 50% on the agg/def bar, which enhances the effectiveness of your green evade skills, and is thus a very good thing.  See lots of Init discussions in other posts for the full scoop.<br>
<br>
To summarize, MAs are no longer the back-up doc, and our standard crit buffs were too uber when cast on other professions (shotgun-toting support classes, anyone?), so they were nerfed to self-only. We were then given a much less-potent but still usefull series of crit-other buffs called the &quot;Mark of [x]&quot; line: &quot;Mark of Risk (+2%)&quot;, &quot;Mark of Danger (+4%)&quot;, and &quot;Mark of Peril (+7%)&quot;.  We still have all of our old crit nanos for ourselves.<br>
<br>
MAs are now coveted in teams due to our superior damage, and the added bonus of a heal now and then when things get hairy.<br>
<br>
I highly recommend anyone who USED to play an MA back in the days of MA ultra-gimpdom to check them out now.  We pretty much kick ass nowadays.<br>
<br>
- iccusion <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#99CC66><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/bthepunchingbag74708.showUserPublicProfile?gid=pantherfan69>Pantherfan69</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Peking Duck</span><br>  Posts: 112<br> <font color=#660000>(10/23/02 9:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2144.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> thanks!</span><hr size=1> Wow, that reply was even more then I had hoped for! Thank you very much for that well written post <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
