/db.php?cmd=view&amp;id=204104&amp;t=ag">Free Movement</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> are sold in the same medical kiosks as first aid stims and nano/treatment labs.  Gotta have 'em now.  They use 1st Aid and Comp Lit, so usually Comp Lit is gonna be the limiting factor for most folks.<br>
<br>
They knock X seconds off of the various root/snare/mezz lines, and the amount of time they reduce goes up as Q level goes up, obviously.<br>
<br>
As for them hitting you with the damn roots/snares right before they die...yeah, that BLOWS.  I recommend you do what I usually do...open the fight with Brawl and continue to wail away...and then as the mob gets close to death (&lt;25% health) don't immediately hit brawl again when it refreshes...save it for when the bastard starts to cast that crap or once you think the brawl can take them out.  A lot of the time you can hit brawl and finish them before they get it off.  Works pretty well.<br>
<br>
And as mentioned, if you set the mission slider to full Physical (rather than mystical), you'll get mostly melee types and few casting mobs.  But the melee types typically hit a LOT harder, so keep that in mind. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
