 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#99CC66><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/bthepunchingbag74708.showUserPublicProfile?gid=viirruss>Viirruss</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Peking Duck</span><br>  Posts: 101<br> <font color=#660000>(4/26/03 4:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2144.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: hmm </span><hr size=1> To answer your question. Yes, FC has stopped screwing with proffession balancing for the most part. If you check the last <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.anarchy-online.com/content/game/inproduction/live/" target="top">patch notes</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->, the MA got a little tweak to crit damage, the halved crit chance in PvP has been removed for fist attacks, but not MA weapons.<br>
<br>
If the constant change bothers you, there have been and are still many game mechanics changes taking place.<br>
<br>
The shadowlands are going to be like a completely new game. Much of our current technology ceases to function there. Of course, you don't have to go to SL's if you don't want to, but I think it could really make us old timers to feel like we are getting a new game! Notum wars is neat, but not really all I thought it would be. They did seem to balance tower fighting though, I think. Outside buffs are much harder to get and keep now. Also, teaming does not change the Pvp level range you are allowed to attack. Hopefully making the battles a little less one sided just because one org/side has a bunch of L200 characters at the battle, who are actually way out of level range to participate fairly. I think this is a good change, though it does lower the probability of being able to defend your towers:/<br>
<br>
Also implants can now be made in excess of QL200, they are a bit hard to put together since you cant buy ANY of the components. The parts all must be <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.aodb.info/search.asp?Search=True&amp;ItemName=refined&amp;ShowPage=1&amp;ShowClusters=True" target="top">Refined</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->. There are alot of neato new clusters out there though. Including but not limited to heal delta, nano regen delta, NCU, % damage Boosts, etc.<br>
<br>
There also may be some new armors you are interested in. There is <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.aodb.info/search.asp?Search=True&amp;ItemName=armed+forces&amp;ShowPage=1" target="top">Omni-armed forces</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->, if you are omni. <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://home.c2i.net/ellusion/armor_omniaf.html" target="top">Here's how ya get it.</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->Then there's all the <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.aodb.info/search.asp?Search=True&amp;ItemName=azure+reveries&amp;ShowPage=1" target="top">Azure</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> stuff. /me drools<br>
<br>
Oh and for StorminSAO and anyone else who has recently come back and maybe lost some item from their inventory. FC now tracks and reimburses lost items if it can be proven. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.anarchy-online.com/character/bio/d/1/name/viirruss">Viirruss</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
